                  <Text layoutX="52.0" layoutY="208.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="A computer system is a combination of hardware, software, data, and users working together to perform tasks. It is not just the machine on your desk, but everything involved in making it work—from the physical parts to the programs and the people who operate them. For example, when you open a word processor to write a document, the hardware (keyboard, CPU, monitor) works together with the software (the word processor) to accept your input, process it, and show the result." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
