                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="52.0" layoutY="500.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="There are two main components in a computer system: hardware and software. Hardware includes all the physical parts like the central processing unit (CPU), memory (RAM), monitor, keyboard, mouse, and storage devices (HDD/SSD). Software refers to the instructions that run on the hardware, such as the operating system (like Windows or Linux) and application programs (like browsers or games). For example, clicking a file icon (hardware action) tells the operating system (software) to open that file using the right program." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
