                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="52.0" layoutY="916.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="To understand how a computer works, we use the IPO model—Input, Process, Output, and Storage. Input is the data you give the system (like typing on a keyboard). Processing is what the CPU does with that input (like calculating or formatting). Output is the result shown to you (like displaying on the screen), and storage is where data is saved for future use." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
