                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="52.0" layoutY="1438.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="The Operating System (OS) is the most important software in a computer. It manages hardware resources and allows you to run other programs. Examples include Windows, macOS, Linux, and Android. Software is divided into system software (like the OS) and application software (like Microsoft Excel or video games). For instance, when you open a browser, the OS manages memory and CPU usage so the browser runs smoothly." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="1590.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="1.5 Importance of Computer Systems in Daily Life" textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
