                  <Text layoutX="52.0" layoutY="1627.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Computer systems are used everywhere—from education and healthcare to banking and entertainment. Understanding how they work helps you become more confident in using them and prepares you for future topics like programming, troubleshooting, and networking. For example, knowing how memory and storage differ can help you fix performance issues or choose the right device for your needs. In the next chapter, we will dive deeper into data representation and how computers understand and manipulate information using binary." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
